    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-12-13T13:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-13T13:30:00-05:00" n="520"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d520">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">831.24/75: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Venezuela</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Corrigan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Caracas</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-13T14:00:00-04:30"
                            >December 13, 1941—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 6:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>301. The Foreign Minister<note n="14" xml:id="d520fn14">C. Parra Pérez.</note>
                    has just requested me to urge the most prompt action in supplying the following
                    listed material to be used for defense of the oil fields<note n="15"
                        xml:id="d520fn15">For correspondence regarding the concern of the United
                        States over the defense of the oil fields in Venezuela, see <ref
                            target="#pg_607">pp. 607</ref> ff.</note> already requested through the
                    Venezuelan Embassy Washington: 4 sets of anti-aircraft machine guns caliber 0.50
                    including 16 pieces; 4 anti-aircraft batteries 37 millimeters including 16
                    pieces; 2,000 shells for each 37 millimeters cannon; 20,000 cartridges for each
                    0.50 machine gun. In order to expedite rapid delivery of this material it was
                    requested that it be sent from one of our bases in the Caribbean. I urge prompt
                    action.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Corrigan</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
